{"id":92,"date":"2022-11-07T17:04:01","date_gmt":"2022-11-07T17:04:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/llgt.cafe\/?p=92"},"modified":"2022-11-07T17:04:01","modified_gmt":"2022-11-07T17:04:01","slug":"teddy-bear-day","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/llgt.cafe\/teddy-bear-day","title":{"rendered":"Teddy Bear Day"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Today is Hug a Bear Day. You may know the story about President Theodore Roosevelt\u2019s encounter with a black bear that helped inspire the creation of the teddy bear, but there are some other things that you may not know about the famed teddy bear.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bear hug was first used in 1846, long before the teddy bears existed. The term Arctophile is used to describe someone who loves collecting teddy bears.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Teddy bears are thought to help build self esteem and help promote creativity in the owners.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In 1995, Magellin T Bear became to first teddy bear to travel into space, aboard the Space Shuttle Discovery.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The German toy company, Sterff, created 50 teddy bears to honor the victims of the 1912 sinking of the Titanic.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Benjamin is my bear. The pictures below are from some of our recent adventures.  I got him in 2012. He and I have been many places together.  Do you have a teddy bear? If so, don\u2019t forget to give it a hug.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" data-id=\"95\" src=\"https:\/\/llgt.cafe\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/Benjamin-1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-95\" srcset=\"https:\/\/llgt.cafe\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/Benjamin-1-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/llgt.cafe\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/Benjamin-1-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/llgt.cafe\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/Benjami